1
00:00:30,650 --> 00:00:33,750
<i>It's an important and popular fact</i>

2
00:00:33,850 --> 00:00:37,750
<i>that things are not always
what they seem.</i>

3
00:00:37,850 --> 00:00:41,650
<i>For instance, on the planet Earth,
man had always assumed</i>

4
00:00:41,750 --> 00:00:45,300
<i>that he was the most intelligent
species occupying the planet,</i>

5
00:00:45,400 --> 00:00:48,050
<i>instead of the third most intelligent.</i>

6
00:00:48,150 --> 00:00:52,650
<i>The second most intelligent creatures were,
of course, dolphins, who, curiously enough,</i>

7
00:00:52,750 --> 00:00:56,650
<i>had long known of the impending
destruction of the planet Earth.</i>

8
00:00:56,750 --> 00:00:59,200
<i>They'd made many attempts
to alert mankind to the danger,</i>

9
00:00:59,300 --> 00:01:02,150
<i>but most of their communications
were misinterpreted</i>

10
00:01:02,250 --> 00:01:05,750
<i>as amusing attempts to punch footballs
or whistle for tidbits.</i>

11
00:01:05,850 --> 00:01:10,300
<i>So, they eventually decided they would
leave Earth by their own means.</i>

12
00:01:10,400 --> 00:01:13,600
<i>The last ever dolphin message
was misinterpreted</i>

13
00:01:13,700 --> 00:01:16,900
<i>as a surprisingly sophisticated attempt
to do a double backward somersault</i>

14
00:01:17,050 --> 00:01:20,050
<i>through a hoop, while whistling
the 'Star-Spangled Banner'.</i>

15
00:01:20,150 --> 00:01:21,900
<i>But in fact, the message was this...</i>

16
00:01:22,000 --> 00:01:24,900
<i>"So long and thanks for all the fish."</i>

