00:49:45,500 --> 00:49:47,550
if memory serves, you won,

653
00:49:47,650 --> 00:49:50,950
proving that good looks and charm win

654
00:49:51,050 --> 00:49:55,950
over brilliance and the ability to govern.

655
00:50:00,250 --> 00:50:03,500
And, incidentally, you are stupid.

656
00:50:03,600 --> 00:50:06,150
Excuse me, excuse me, Mr. Humma, sir.

657
00:50:07,700 --> 00:50:10,400
I just want to say, there's been
some sort of terrible mix up, hasn't it?

658
00:50:10,500 --> 00:50:12,900
'Cause, actually, he's not with us.

659
00:50:13,000 --> 00:50:15,900
We came to worship you.
He followed us and...

660
00:50:16,000 --> 00:50:18,600
He grew, didn't he. He's not that tall.

661
00:50:18,700 --> 00:50:23,850
You didn't come half-way across the galaxy
to settle a campaign grudge, Zaphod.

662
00:50:25,350 --> 00:50:27,400
Why are you here?

663
00:50:29,000 --> 00:50:31,650
Of course not. That's... that's ridiculous.

664
00:50:31,750 --> 00:50:36,000
I've been stranded on a strange planet
for a number of years.

664
00:50:36,100 --> 00:50:37,400
I haven't been avoiding you.

665
00:50:37,500 --> 00:50:40,500
You look great. You're doing well.

666
00:50:40,600 --> 00:50:42,250
You've grown, obviously.

667
00:50:42,700 --> 00:50:46,400
Wait, wait, wait, wait, wait!
We don't know why we're here.

668
00:50:46,550 --> 00:50:50,100
We were trying to get to Magrathea,
and our ship brought us here.

669
00:50:51,700 --> 00:50:55,150
How very, very improbable.

670
00:51:02,600 --> 00:51:05,400
I kept a few souvenirs from my former life.

671
00:51:05,500 --> 00:51:08,400
The heady days of space piracy.

672
00:51:09,400 --> 00:51:16,200
But even an Infinite Improbability
Drive requires coordinates.

673
00:51:16,300 --> 00:51:18,700
Which I happen to have.

674
00:51:18,850 --> 00:51:20,400
No, no, no.

675
00:51:20,550 --> 00:51:22,950
