760
00:56:33,300 --> 00:56:34,700
Thanks very much, Marv!

765
00:57:20,500 --> 00:57:22,000
Magrathea!

765
00:57:22,500 --> 00:57:24,800
- No. We're on the Vogon planet.
- Yes!

766
00:57:24,900 --> 00:57:27,500
- Yes, it is! It's Magrathea!
- This is Vogsphere.

767
00:57:27,600 --> 00:57:29,500
Yeah, Magrathea!

767
00:57:29,600 --> 00:57:30,800
- No, it's not.
- Yes it is! I know it is!

768
00:57:30,900 --> 00:57:34,400
- There is no Magrathea.
- Yes, it is! Yes, it is!

769
00:57:35,500 --> 00:57:37,700
- What are you doing?
- They took my head.

770
00:57:37,800 --> 00:57:40,500
- They have these on Arcturan mega freighters.
- They took my head.

771
00:57:40,600 --> 00:57:43,250
Captains use them when
they really need to concentrate.

772
00:57:43,350 --> 00:57:46,200
- What is it?
- It's a thinking cap.

773
00:57:50,350 --> 00:57:52,000
There you go.

774
00:57:56,550 --> 00:58:00,250
It should give him some zest
for about ten minutes or so.

775
00:58:00,350 --> 00:58:04,800
Now I'm feeling much better
about our predicament.

776
00:58:25,150 --> 00:58:29,250
By the way, I checked the Guide for the best
way to rescue a prisoner from Vogsphere.

777
00:58:29,350 --> 00:58:32,550
It said don't.
I'm assuming you have a better plan.

778
00:58:32,650 --> 00:58:35,150
Well, I kind of had this idea that we could...

779
00:58:37,200 --> 00:58:39,500
- Did anyone see that?
- See what?

780
00:58:39,600 --> 00:58:41,500
- What was it?
- Huh!

781
00:58:41,600 --> 00:58:45,900
Nothing, it's... nothing.
It's just my imagination.

782
00:58:46,000 --> 00:58:50,200
Okay, right now, stop! Everyone just
stop a minute, please, and look at me.

783
00:58:50,300 --> 00:58:55,200
There's... definitely
something going on here.

784
00:58:55,300 --> 00:58:57,300
Just... just watch.

785
00:58:59,300 --> 00:59:02,750
Just watch.

786
00:59:04,700 --> 00:59:07,150
Okay, I think we...

787
00:59:08,200 --> 00:59:09,350
Ah-ha! You too!

788
00:59:11,100 --> 00:59:13,400
Yeah, what was that?

789
00:59:13,500 --> 00:59:15,550
I thi...

790
00:59:16,800 --> 00:59:18,800
Zaphod, what do you think?

791
00:59:22,100 --> 00:59:23,200
I think...

791
00:59:24,000 --> 00:59:26,800
Zarquon! What was that? Jeez!

792
00:59:26,950 --> 00:59:30,550
I'd make a suggestion,
but you wouldn't listen.

793
00:59:30,650 --> 00:59:33,550
- No one ever does.
- I have an idea.

794
00:59:35,500 --> 00:59:37,500
Ford! Kill it! Get rid of it!

795
00:59:45,200 --> 00:59:48,000
Okay, don't think.

796
00:59:48,100 --> 00:59:50,600
Nobody think. No ideas.

797
00:59:50,700 --> 00:59:52,850
No theories. No nothing.

799
00:59:59,050 --> 01:00:01,650
This is crazy!
Trillian is in there somewhere.

800
01:00:01,750 --> 01:00:04,400
And we need an idea to help save her.

800
01:00:04,500 --> 01:00:06,550
I have an ide...

801
01:00:06,800 --> 01:00:08,800
Run!

803
01:00:38,150 --> 01:00:40,250
You're supposed to stop.

804
01:00:49,500 --> 01:00:53,800
Okay, so I'm not thinking.
Not thinking. No ideas coming.

805
01:00:56,600 --> 01:00:59,750
All right, this isn't an idea
that has any merit at all,

806
01:00:59,850 --> 01:01:03,500
but, Marvin, can you give me a hand?

807
01:01:06,200 --> 01:01:08,300
Okay, where is she?!

808
01:01:11,300 --> 01:01:14,150
Who, the director of robot arm repair?

809
01:01:15,850 --> 01:01:20,350
