Thank you.

878
01:05:59,000 --> 01:06:02,100
She's free to go.

879
01:06:02,200 --> 01:06:05,400
Release her.

880
01:06:07,050 --> 01:06:10,900
Zaphod's here. Well then, that's fine then.

880
01:06:11,000 --> 01:06:12,500
Let's just go and him.

881
01:06:17,650 --> 01:06:20,350
Who are we waiting for again?

882
01:06:24,400 --> 01:06:25,700
No, I'm serious.

883
01:06:28,400 --> 01:06:30,650
Tricia!

884
01:06:33,700 --> 01:06:36,250
- Tricia!
- Trill.

885
01:06:36,350 --> 01:06:39,250
- Hey, come on.
- You idiot!

886
01:06:39,350 --> 01:06:41,350
You signed the order to destroy Earth.

887
01:06:41,450 --> 01:06:43,300
- He did?!
- I did?

888
01:06:43,400 --> 01:06:47,850
Yes. "Love and kisses, Zaphod"?
You didn't even read it, did you?

889
01:06:47,950 --> 01:06:52,750
Honey, I'm President of the Galaxy.
I don't get a lot of time for reading.

890
01:06:54,850 --> 01:06:56,650
An entire planet, my home,

891
01:06:56,750 --> 01:06:59,400
destroyed all because you thought
somebody wanted your autograph!

892
01:06:59,500 --> 01:07:02,700
- Honey, they framed me!
- Are you an idiot?! Serously?!

893
01:07:02,800 --> 01:07:06,700
- Trillian!
- You knew. Why didn't you tell me?

894
01:07:06,800 --> 01:07:10,900
- He threatened me.
- Get a backbone, Arthur.

895
01:07:11,000 --> 01:07:16,150
Oh, a backbone? What about coming
here to rescue you? Thank you. My idea.

896
01:07:17,350 --> 01:07:20,000
Stupid!

897
01:07:23,650 --> 01:07:26,000
- Got your arm.
- How considerate.

898
01:07:26,100 --> 01:07:30,450
Right, then, all those of you lucky enough
to have two arms, hold tight.

899
01:07:46,500 --> 01:07:50,300
The President tests my patience.

900
01:07:50,400 --> 01:07:55,200
This time I shall pursue him myself.
Ready my ship.

901
01:07:55,300 --> 01:07:58,250
Fantastic. At last.

902
01:08:02,850 --> 01:08:06,850
Oh! That's one hour for lunch, everybody.

903
01:08:07,700 --> 01:08:11,150
I think I'll have soup today.

904
01:08:11,900 --> 01:08:15,400
<i>The Encyclopedia Galactica,
in its chapter on love,</i>

905
01:08:15,500 --> 01:08:18,900
<i>states that it is
far too complicated to define.</i>

906
01:08:19,000 --> 01:08:23,450
<i>'The Hitchhiker's Guide to the Galaxy'
has this to say on the subject of love.</i>

907
01:08:23,550 --> 01:08:26,050
<i>"Avoid, if at all possible."</i>

908
01:08:26,150 --> 01:08:29,050
<i>Unfortunately, Arthur Dent has never read</i>

909
01:08:29,150 --> 01:08:31,600
<i>'The Hitchhiker's Guide to the Galaxy'.</i>

910
01:08:31,750 --> 01:08:35,700
- Oh, I'm so sorry.
- No, come in.

911
01:08:35,800 --> 01:08:38,050
I didn't...

912
01:08:41,000 --> 01:08:42,650
Look...

913
01:08:42,750 --> 01:08:45,700
Trillian, I just wanted to say,
you were right, of course.

914
01:08:45,800 --> 01:08:50,600
I should've told you, and I understand
totally if you're angry with me.

915
01:08:50,700 --> 01:08:55,100
For what it's worth,
I know how you must be feeling.

916
01:08:56,850 --> 01:09:01,200
- Can you hand me a towel?
- Yeah, sure, this...

917
01:09:02,650 --> 01:09:04,650
Thank you.

918
01:09:04,750 --> 01:09:07,750
Actually, what I was gonna say was...

919
01:09:09,050 --> 01:09:14,100
if I'd said yes to you
and gone to Madagascar,

920
01:09:14,200 --> 01:09:18,050
then neither of us would be here now.

921
01:09:18,150 --> 01:09:21,900
I just thought that might count for something.

922
01:09:25,300 --> 01:09:27,200
It doesn't matter.

923
01:09:50,250 --> 01:09:55,850
All right, computer, take us to...
Where we headed again?

924
01:09:55,950 --> 01:09:59,350
Okay, I'm gonna get you another lemon.

925
01:09:59,450 --> 01:10:01,450
All right.

926
01:10:05,050 --> 01:10:08,150
<i>Engaging Improbability Drive.</i>

927
01:10:08,250 --> 01:10:12,150
No, no, no. Zaphod, no.
Buttons are not toys. What did you do?

928
01:10:12,250 --> 01:10:14,100
<i>Magrathean coordinates accepted.</i>

929
01:10:21,950 --> 01:10:24,550
<i>Guys, it just blows my circuits to tell you</i>

930
01:10:24,650 --> 01:10:28,050
<i>that we're currently in an orbit
at an altitude of 300 miles,</i>

931
01:10:28,150 --> 01:10:31,800
<i>around the legendary planet of Magrathea.</i>

932
01:10:31,900 --> 01:10:34,600
Magrathea! Magrathea!

933
01:10:35,750 --> 01:10:38,000
Magrathea!

934
01:10:41,300 --> 01:10:42,500
Unbelievable.

935
01:10:45,750 --> 01:10:48,500
Incredible.

936
01:10:48,700 --> 01:10:51,250
It's even worse than I thought it would be.

937
01:10:52,450 --> 01:10:56,750
<i>Greetings. This is a recorded announcement
as we are all out at the moment.</i>

938
01:10:56,850 --> 01:11:00,300
<i>The Commercial Council of Magrathea
thanks you for your esteemed visit,</i>

939
01:11:00,400 --> 01:11:03,750
<i>but regrets that the entire planet
is temporarily closed.</i>

940
01:11:03,850 --> 01:11:07,650
<i>If you would like to leave your name
and a planet where you can be contacted,</i>

941
01:11:07,750 --> 01:11:09,800
<i>kindly do so at the tone.</i>

942
01:11:10,950 --> 01:11:14,850
- How can a planet be closed?
- Zarkin' A, cousin.

943
01:11:14,950 --> 01:11:18,350
Okay, computer, keep going. Take us down.

944
01:11:18,500 --> 01:11:20,050
<i>I'd be happy to.</i>

945
01:11:21,700 --> 01:11:24,350
<i>It is most gratifying that your enthusiasm</i>

946
01:11:24,450 --> 01:11:26,500
<i>for our planet continues unabated.</i>

947
01:11:26,900 --> 01:11:29,500
<i>As a token of our appreciation,</i>

948
01:11:29,600 --> 01:11:32,600
<i>we hope you will enjoy
the two thermo-nuclear missiles</i>

949
01:11:32,700 --> 01:11:36,000
<i>we've just sent
to converge with your craft.</i>

950
01:11:36,750 --> 01:11:39,150
<i>To ensure on-going quality of service,</i>

951
01:11:39,250 --> 01:11:43,450
<i>your death may be monitored
for training purposes. Thank you.</i>

952
01:11:43,550 --> 01:11:45,500
<i>Guys, I'm delighted to tell you</i>

953
01:11:45,600 --> 01:11:48,450
<i>that there are two thermo-nuclear
missiles heading right for us.</i>

954
01:11:48,550 --> 01:11:51,850
<i>If you don't mind, I'm gonna go ahead
and take evasive action.</i>

955
01:11:56,200 --> 01:11:59,400
<i>There seems to be something
jamming my guidance system.</i>

956
01:11:59,500 --> 01:12:01,500
<i>Impact minus 45 seconds.</i>

957
01:12:05,250 --> 01:12:07,400
Computer, do something!

958
01:12:07,550 --> 01:12:11,800
<i>Sure thing, fella. Handing over
manual control. Good luck!</i>

959
01:12:22,400 --> 01:12:24,000
I need some help!

960
01:12:25,400 --> 01:12:27,900
I can't do this without my third arm.

961
01:12:30,500 --> 01:12:33,000
Arthur, grab my hand!

962
01:12:43,450 --> 01:12:47,150
- Did we lose 'em?
- No, they're coming right at us.

963
01:12:49,800 --> 01:12:53,500
- Why don't I just press this thing?!
- No, we're not fully back to normal yet!

964
01:12:53,600 --> 01:12:55,600
- So, what will happen then?!
- I don't know!

965
01:12:55,700 --> 01:12:59,700
No! Don't do it! We're here.
No telling where it'll send us. Don't do it.

966
01:13:03,200 --> 01:13:04,650
- Sod it all.
- No!

967
01:13:08,650 --> 01:13:12,000
Wow! Where are we?

968
01:13:16,200 --> 01:13:19,000
Exactly where we were.

969
01:13:19,350 --> 01:13:20,650
And the missiles?

970
01:13:21,700 --> 01:13:27,250
Apparently, they've turned
into a bowl of petunias.

971
01:13:27,850 --> 01:13:31,600
And a very surprised-looking whale.

972
01:13:31,700 --> 01:13:39,000
<i>And an improbability factor
of 8,767,128 to 1 against.</i>

973
01:13:39,900 --> 01:13:42,800
We have normality.

974
01:13:42,900 --> 01:13:45,300
Normality, right.

975
01:13:45,400 --> 01:13:48,300
We can talk about normality
till the cows come home.

976
01:13:49,500 --> 01:13:52,500
- What is normal?
- What's home?

977
01:13:52,650 --> 01:13:54,300
What are cows?

978
01:13:55,500 --> 01:13:58,350
A proper cup of tea
would restore my normality.

979
01:13:58,450 --> 01:14:02,700
<i>It is important to note that,
suddenly and against all probability,</i>

980
01:14:02,800 --> 01:14:05,700
<i>a sperm whale had been
called into existence</i>

981
01:14:05,800 --> 01:14:09,850
<i>several miles above
the surface of an alien planet.</i>

982
01:14:09,950 --> 01:14:12,800
<i>And since this is not a naturally
tenable position for a whale,</i>

983
01:14:12,900 --> 01:14:17,900
<i>this innocent creature had very little
time to come to terms with its identity.</i>

984
01:14:18,000 --> 01:14:20,550
<i>This is what it thought as it fell...</i>

985
01:14:21,000 --> 01:14:23,850
Whoa! What's happening? Who am I?

986
01:14:23,950 --> 01:14:27,600
Why am I here? What's my purpose in life?
What do I mean by who am I?

987
01:14:27,750 --> 01:14:29,850
Okay, okay. Calm down, calm down.
Get a grip now.

988
01:14:29,950 --> 01:14:34,000
Ooh, this is an interesting sensation.
What is it? It is a sort of tingling in my...

989
01:14:34,100 --> 01:14:39,150
Well, I suppose I better start finding names
for things. Let's call it a... tail. Yeah, tail!

990
01:14:39,300 --> 01:14:43,350
And, hey, what's this roaring sound whooshing
past what I'm suddenly gonna call my head?

991
01:14:43,450 --> 01:14:45,550
Wind. Is that a good name? That'll do.

992
01:14:45,650 --> 01:14:48,900
Yay, this is really exciting.
I'm dizzy with anticipation.

993
01:14:49,000 --> 01:14:51,550
Or is it the wind?
There's a lot of that now, isn't it?

994
01:14:51,650 --> 01:14:55,700
And what's this thing coming towards me
very fast? So big and flat and round.

995
01:14:55,850 --> 01:15:00,900
It needs a big wide-sounding name
like ow, ound, round, ground!

996
01:15:01,050 --> 01:15:05,550
That's it, ground! I wonder if it'll be
friends with me. Hello, ground.

997
01:15:07,950 --> 01:15:11,750
<i>Curiously, the only thing that went
through the mind of the bowl of petunias</i>

998
01:15:11,850 --> 01:15:15,850
<i>as it fell was, "Oh, no, not again!"</i>

999
01:15:17,100 --> 01:15:22,750
<i>Many have speculated that if we knew exactly
why the bowl of petunias had thought that,</i>

1000
01:15:22,850 --> 01:15:28,200
<i>we should know a lot more about the
nature of the universe than we do now.</i>

1001
01:15:32,550 --> 01:15:34,800
What are those things?

1002
01:15:34,900 --> 01:15:38,250
They're portals to another dimension.

1003
01:15:38,350 --> 01:15:42,850
Right. I don't suppose this portal
has central heating, does it?

1004
01:15:48,200 --> 01:15:50,650
Ah, this is the one.

1005
01:15:50,800 --> 01:15:55,000
This will all end in tears, I just know it.

1006
01:15:58,100 --> 01:16:00,300
Right here.

1007
01:16:00,400 --> 01:16:02,000
Hey! Whoa!

1008
01:16:04,700 --> 01:16:07,150
Okay, in we go!

1009
01:16:07,250 --> 01:16:12,350
We can't just step into that... that!
We don't know where it leads.

1010
01:16:12,450 --> 01:16:14,600
If we pick the wrong one,

1011
01:16:14,700 --> 01:16:18,450
we just... we come back,
we pick another one. It's no biggie.

1012
01:16:18,550 --> 01:16:22,150
What?! Yeah, it's a big biggie, Ford.
A big biggie!

1013
01:16:22,250 --> 01:16:27,200
I mean, what if it rips us all into
tiny little atomic particle thingies?!

1014
01:16:27,300 --> 01:16:30,850
This is the right one. I have a hunch.

1015
01:16:30,950 --> 01:16:35,150
- Ford!
- His hunches are good.

1016
01:16:35,250 --> 01:16:37,650
Arthur, I say we go.

1017
01:16:37,750 --> 01:16:43,600
Go with the hunch of a man
whose brain is fuelled by lemons?!

1018
01:16:43,700 --> 01:16:45,350
This is suicide!

1019
01:16:45,450 --> 01:16:49,450
- I think I resent that.
- I don't care what you think you think.

1020
01:16:49,550 --> 01:16:52,450
I'm getting a lot of hostility from you,
Alex or...

1021
01:16:52,550 --> 01:16:56,100
- Arthur!
- Have you ever tried yoga?

1022
01:16:57,300 --> 01:17:00,900
- Trillian!
- I think that's supposed to happen.

1023
01:17:05,750 --> 01:17:09,000
She's gone! Ford, she's gone!

1024
01:17:09,250 --> 01:17:12,250
Arthur, don't panic!

1025
01:17:13,950 --> 01:17:17,900
- Ford!
- Hey, wait for me!

1028
01:17:33,300 --> 01:17:39,300
Idiot! Come on, come on, come on!

1030
01:18:00,350 --> 01:18:04,000
No, no, no, don't leave.
Come on, come on, just start!

1031
01:18:04,100 --> 01:18:07,250
I told you this would end in tears.

1032
01:18:07,350 --> 01:18:09,450
Did you?! Did you?!

1033
01:18:18,000 --> 01:18:20,450
Geronimo!

1035
01:18:23,150 --> 01:18:27,000
Far out! Far out!

1036
01:18:27,750 --> 01:18:32,450
This is it! This is it!
Deep Thought. I'm a-coming.

1037
01:18:35,250 --> 01:18:41,550
So, this is how it's all going to end, is it, ey?

1038
01:18:41,650 --> 01:18:46,550
Me, alone on a dead planet,
with a manically depressed robot.

1039
01:18:46,650 --> 01:18:48,100
You think you've got problems.

1040
01:18:48,200 --> 01:18:51,750
What are you supposed to do,
if you are a manically depressed robot?

1041
01:18:51,850 --> 01:18:53,050
Excuse me.

1043
01:19:00,150 --> 01:19:04,750
- Who are you?
- What? No, my name is not important.

1044
01:19:06,300 --> 01:19:08,400
You must come with me.

1045
01:19:08,500 --> 01:19:12,800
- Get away.
- Terrible events are afoot.

1046
01:19:12,900 --> 01:19:16,400
You must come or you'll be late.

1047
01:19:16,500 --> 01:19:18,700
- Late? What for?
- What?

1048
01:19:18,800 --> 01:19:24,350
No, no. What's your name, Earthman?

1049
01:19:25,350 --> 01:19:27,700
- Dent. Arthur Dent.
- Well...

1050
01:19:27,800 --> 01:19:30,800
late as in "the late Dentarthurdent".

1051
01:19:31,250 --> 01:19:35,150
It's a sort of threat, do you see? No.

1052
01:19:35,250 --> 01:19:38,250
- No.
- Your friends are safe.

1053
01:19:38,350 --> 01:19:41,600
- You can trust me.
- Trust a man who won't tell me his name?

1054
01:19:43,000 --> 01:19:46,400
Okay, my name is...

1055
01:19:46,500 --> 01:19:50,700
My name is... Slartibartfast.

1056
01:19:52,600 --> 01:19:55,700
I said it wasn't important.

1057
01:19:57,350 --> 01:20:01,550
Well... so my friends are safe?

1058
01:20:01,650 --> 01:20:03,100
Let me show you.

1059
01:20:03,200 --> 01:20:09,100
I could calculate your chances
of survival, but you won't like it.

1060
01:20:34,050 --> 01:20:36,850
Did you know we built planets?

1061
01:20:36,950 --> 01:20:40,950
Oh, yes! Fascinating trade.

1062
01:20:41,050 --> 01:20:45,700
Doing the coastlines
was always my favorite.

1063
01:20:45,800 --> 01:20:51,450
And we used to have endless fun doing
the little fiddly bits around the fjords.

1064
01:20:51,550 --> 01:20:56,550
But then the galactic economy collapsed,
and seeing that custom-built planets

1065
01:20:56,650 --> 01:21:02,150
are a bit of a luxury commodity...

1066
01:21:02,250 --> 01:21:06,100
Anyway, you must come with me, because
there's been a terrible mix-up with your planet.

1067
01:21:06,200 --> 01:21:08,450
Best laid plans of mice, you know.

1068
01:21:08,550 --> 01:21:12,000
- And men.
- What?

1069
01:21:12,100 --> 01:21:14,050
Best laid plans of mice and men.

1070
01:21:16,000 --> 01:21:18,950
Yes, well, I don't think men have
got much to do with it. Here.

1071
01:21:59,950 --> 01:22:01,900
I must warn you,

1072
01:22:02,000 --> 01:22:05,500
we're going to pass through,
well, a sort of gateway thing.

1073
01:22:05,600 --> 01:22:07,800
- Huh?
- It may disturb you.

1074
01:22:07,900 --> 01:22:11,000
It scares the willies out of me.

1076
01:22:42,000 --> 01:22:45,500
Welcome to our factory floor.

1078
01:23:08,950 --> 01:23:12,400
All right. All right.

1079
01:23:12,500 --> 01:23:15,350
Yeah, this is it.

1080
01:23:18,400 --> 01:23:20,000
This is it.

1081
01:23:21,050 --> 01:23:24,900
O' great Deep Thought!

1082
01:23:25,000 --> 01:23:26,700
We have traveled long...

1083
01:23:28,800 --> 01:23:30,550
and far.

1084
01:23:30,650 --> 01:23:36,150
Have you calculated
the ultimate question of life,

1085
01:23:36,250 --> 01:23:39,000
the universe and everything?

1086
01:23:39,200 --> 01:23:40,450
No.

1087
01:23:40,550 --> 01:23:43,150
- What?
- I've been watching TV.

1088
01:23:43,250 --> 01:23:44,300
Oh.

1089
01:23:44,400 --> 01:23:47,500
I designed another computer to do that.

1090
01:23:47,800 --> 01:23:50,450
Oh, right, I forgot. Is it here?

1091
01:23:50,550 --> 01:23:53,300
No, it's not here. It's another world.

1092
01:23:53,450 --> 01:23:55,550
It's on another world.

1093
01:23:55,650 --> 01:23:59,150
It is another world, stupid.

1094
01:23:59,250 --> 01:24:01,650
Or at least it was until the Vogons destroyed it

1095
01:24:01,750 --> 01:24:04,100
to make way for a hyperspace expressway.

1096
01:24:04,300 --> 01:24:06,550
Well... Okay.

1097
01:24:06,650 --> 01:24:08,750
You sure you don't have the question,

1098
01:24:08,850 --> 01:24:12,350
or a way to, you know, access it or something?

1099
01:24:12,450 --> 01:24:14,400
'Cause I think I've done like a lot to get here.

1100
01:24:14,500 --> 01:24:19,000
Oh, shh, shush! The show's back on.

1101
01:24:23,350 --> 01:24:27,400
Well, I don't wanna bother you,
so I'm gonna... Good stuff.

1102
01:24:27,500 --> 01:24:31,900
Great. I'm gonna go and find something
else for my entire life to be about.

1103
01:24:32,000 --> 01:24:35,250
- Zaphod, Zaphod, there's the gun.
- Yeah?

1104
01:24:35,350 --> 01:24:37,650
- Gun?
- That Humma sent you for.

1105
01:24:37,750 --> 01:24:42,200
- You gave him your head.
- Why'd I do that?

1106
01:24:42,300 --> 01:24:44,000
- Okay.
- That's stupid.

1107
01:24:44,100 --> 01:24:49,200
O' Deep Thought,
we were told that there is a gun.

1108
01:25:04,050 --> 01:25:06,250
- There you are.
- Hmm?

1109
01:25:06,350 --> 01:25:08,050
Look familiar?

1110
01:25:08,150 --> 01:25:11,600
So, it wasn't destroyed?

1111
01:25:11,700 --> 01:25:16,000
Actually, it was. This is a back-up.
Earth Mark II.

1112
01:25:19,100 --> 01:25:20,900
So, you made the Earth?

1113
01:25:21,500 --> 01:25:24,650
Not me alone, but I did my part.

1114
01:25:24,750 --> 01:25:28,000
Ever heard of a place,
