1139
01:26:56,900 --> 01:26:58,950
<i>"You just don't get it, do you?"</i>

1140
01:27:02,000 --> 01:27:04,000
And you're right, I shouldn't be so upset,

1141
01:27:04,100 --> 01:27:06,350
because life goes on, you know,

1142
01:27:06,450 --> 01:27:09,250
and I should just go on with it.

1143
01:27:09,350 --> 01:27:11,600
Shoot him again.

1144
01:27:11,700 --> 01:27:13,000
Whoa!

1145
01:27:14,950 --> 01:27:18,650
Hitchhiking's good. Towels are good too.

1146
01:27:18,750 --> 01:27:22,050
- Say what?
- That is brilliant.

1147
01:27:22,150 --> 01:27:24,200
What's goin'...?

1148
01:27:24,300 --> 01:27:27,100
I can see why Humma Kavula
would want one of these.

1149
01:27:28,350 --> 01:27:31,050
- We better get back. Arthur's waiting.
- Yeah, who cares?

1150
01:27:31,150 --> 01:27:35,700
Well, I do. Especially since we're both somewhat
of an endangered species now, thanks to you.

1151
01:27:35,800 --> 01:27:37,900
Why so edgy, baby doll? Relax.

1152
01:27:38,050 --> 01:27:40,800
Why so edgy?
You wanna know why I'm edgy?

1153
01:27:42,700 --> 01:27:44,850
Of course you're edgy.
Your planet's been blown up

1154
01:27:44,950 --> 01:27:48,600
and you've been tooling around the galaxy
with the guy who signed the order.

1155
01:27:48,700 --> 01:27:50,200
Huh?

1156
01:27:51,000 --> 01:27:53,100
You actually wanted to know the question,

1157
01:27:53,200 --> 01:27:55,700
because you always wondered to know
if there was more to life,

1158
01:27:57,800 --> 01:28:00,000
and now you're crushed,
because you find out there really isn't.

1159
01:28:00,100 --> 01:28:04,650
Hey, fantastic! Psychedelic!

1160
01:28:06,450 --> 01:28:10,200
You've got no home, no family,
and you're stuck with me,

1161
01:28:10,300 --> 01:28:13,900
another in a long line of men
who doesn't really get you.

1162
01:28:14,000 --> 01:28:17,650
Huh? That's not true.

1163
01:28:21,050 --> 01:28:25,450
And you're worried you might have blown it
with the one guy who really does.

1164
01:28:27,150 --> 01:28:28,950
Hey, whoops.

1165
01:28:31,050 --> 01:28:33,700
Oh, baby doll!

1166
01:28:33,800 --> 01:28:36,700
Give me that thing!

1167
01:28:38,600 --> 01:28:42,900
It won't affect me. I'm already a woman.

1168
01:28:54,000 --> 01:28:56,300
Hey, it's okay.
It's only a couple of little mice!

1169
01:29:00,050 --> 01:29:03,550
Voilà! Himalayas! Good, ey?

1170
01:29:07,000 --> 01:29:09,400
Earthman, you must realize

1171
01:29:09,500 --> 01:29:16,000
that the planet you lived on was
commissioned, paid for and run by mice.

1172
01:29:18,800 --> 01:29:22,050
When you're saying mice, do you mean
the little furry white creatures

1173
01:29:22,150 --> 01:29:24,050
with whiskers, ears, cheese?

1174
01:29:24,150 --> 01:29:28,900
Yeah, but then they're protrusions into our dimension
of hyper intelligent pandimensional beings.

1175
01:29:29,000 --> 01:29:32,800
I mean, I don't know this...
cheese of which you speak,

1176
01:29:32,900 --> 01:29:36,650
but they were there on Earth
as mice experimenting on you.

1177
01:29:36,750 --> 01:29:41,650
I see where you've become confused now.
You see, we were experimenting on them.

1178
01:29:41,750 --> 01:29:45,600
Ah, no, well, yeah, no. I gather
that's what they wanted you to think,

1179
01:29:45,700 --> 01:29:49,000
but you were actually elements
in their computer program.

1180
01:29:51,350 --> 01:29:53,800
Actually, this explains a lot, you know.

1181
01:29:53,900 --> 01:29:56,550
All my life, I've had this strange feeling

1182
01:29:56,650 --> 01:29:59,650
that there's something big and
sinister going on in the world.

1183
01:29:59,750 --> 01:30:03,500
No, that's perfectly normal paranoia.
Everyone in the universe gets that.

1184
01:30:06,850 --> 01:30:10,350
Perhaps I'm old and tired,
but I think that the chances of finding out

1185
01:30:10,450 --> 01:30:13,150
what's actually going on
are so absurdly remote

1186
01:30:13,250 --> 01:30:17,350
that the only thing to do is say hang
the sense of it and keep yourself busy.

1187
01:30:17,450 --> 01:30:19,900
I'd much rather be happy than right any day.

1188
01:30:20,000 --> 01:30:21,950
- And are you?
- No.

1189
01:30:22,050 --> 01:30:24,700
Well, that's where it all falls down, of course.

1190
01:30:36,000 --> 01:30:37,500
Here you are then.

1191
01:30:52,600 --> 01:30:54,250
Is this...?

1192
01:31:08,250 --> 01:31:10,500
It's all there.

1193
01:31:11,650 --> 01:31:13,850
You know, it all works.

1194
01:31:13,950 --> 01:31:16,000
Welcome home.

1195
01:31:35,600 --> 01:31:37,900
- Hey!
- Hey, man!

1196
01:31:38,050 --> 01:31:40,100
- There you are!
- Surprise!

1197
01:31:40,200 --> 01:31:43,150
What are you doing?
What happened to you?

1198
01:31:43,250 --> 01:31:44,700
Is that tea?

1199
01:31:44,800 --> 01:31:48,700
- First, our hosts attacked us.
- Right.

1200
01:31:48,800 --> 01:31:52,700
But then they made up for it by making us...

1201
01:31:52,800 --> 01:31:55,050
this amazing meal.

1202
01:31:56,100 --> 01:31:59,300
It's so... Everything's right.
Everything's delicious.

1203
01:32:00,900 --> 01:32:03,600
Oh, come on, that's lovely.

1204
01:32:03,700 --> 01:32:05,950
We're glad you like it, Earth creature.

1205
01:32:10,150 --> 01:32:14,800
The... talking... talking mice. Cool.

1206
01:32:14,950 --> 01:32:20,050
- Sit, Earthman.
- Oh, thank you. Thank you for that.

1207
01:32:21,050 --> 01:32:24,450
- Please, drink.
- Excuse me.

1208
01:32:24,550 --> 01:32:27,950
- Is there anything else?
- No, we're quite happy, thank you.

1209
01:32:28,050 --> 01:32:31,750
Good, I'll be outside, so...

1210
01:32:31,850 --> 01:32:34,050
You were right.

1211
01:32:34,150 --> 01:32:35,950
- Please, drink.
- Yes.

1212
01:32:36,600 --> 01:32:38,550
He was right.

1213
01:32:38,700 --> 01:32:40,500
Now, to business.

1214
01:32:40,600 --> 01:32:42,400
- To business!
- To business!

1215
01:32:42,500 --> 01:32:43,800
- Eat!
- Eat!

1216
01:32:43,900 --> 01:32:45,650
- Shh.
- Sorry.

1217
01:32:45,750 --> 01:32:46,900
As you know, we've spent a lot of time on
your planet looking for this ultimate question.

1219
01:32:50,000 --> 01:32:53,950
Only to have it blow up in our faces, literally.

1220
01:32:54,050 --> 01:32:57,300
Which is why you're here.
We've been offered a lucrative contract

1221
01:32:57,400 --> 01:32:59,650
- to do several 5-D TV chat shows.
- Right.

1222
01:32:59,750 --> 01:33:02,300
But here's the point.
We must have product.

1223
01:33:02,400 --> 01:33:05,600
We need the ultimate question,
or at least one that sounds ultimate.

1224
01:33:05,700 --> 01:33:07,750
- Of course.
- Yes, we've rebuilt the planet,

1225
01:33:07,850 --> 01:33:11,000
and now all we need is
the missing piece of the puzzle.

1226
01:33:11,100 --> 01:33:13,250
- Which happens to be your brain.
- Right.

1227
01:33:13,350 --> 01:33:14,650
More tea?

1228
01:33:14,750 --> 01:33:17,450
Sorry, did you just say you need my brain?

1229
01:33:17,550 --> 01:33:19,800
Yes, to complete the program.

1230
01:33:22,800 --> 01:33:25,550
Okay. You can't have my brain. I'm using it.

1231
01:33:25,650 --> 01:33:30,450
- Hardly.
- Hardly? Cheeky... Cheeky mouse.

1232
01:33:34,950 --> 01:33:37,500
Zaphod! Trillian!

1233
01:33:38,000 --> 01:33:39,900
Ford.

1234
01:33:40,000 --> 01:33:41,450
What was in that food?

1235
01:33:42,000 --> 01:33:45,300
What was in my tea?

1236
01:33:45,400 --> 01:33:48,000
Don't worry. You won't feel a thing.

1237
01:33:51,450 --> 01:33:53,450
Just wait a sodding minute!

1238
01:33:53,600 --> 01:33:56,100
You want a question
that goes with the answer 42?

1239
01:33:56,200 --> 01:33:57,850
What about, what's 6x7?

1240
01:33:57,950 --> 01:34:01,500
Or... how many Vogons does
it take to change a light bulb?

1241
01:34:01,600 --> 01:34:05,400
Here's one, how many roads
must a man walk down?

1242
01:34:06,800 --> 01:34:08,750
Hey, that's not bad!

1243
01:34:08,850 --> 01:34:10,000
Fine.

1243
01:34:11,800 --> 01:34:15,250
Fine, take it, 'cause my head
is filled with questions,

1244
01:34:15,350 --> 01:34:17,600
and, I can ssure you,
no answer to any one of them

1245
01:34:17,700 --> 01:34:21,300
has ever brought me one iota of happiness.

1246
01:34:21,400 --> 01:34:22,950
Except for one.

1247
01:34:23,050 --> 01:34:26,000
The one. The only question
I've ever wanted an answer to.

1248
01:34:26,100 --> 01:34:27,700
Is she the one?

1249
01:34:28,800 --> 01:34:32,250
The answer bloody well isn't 42, it's yes.

1250
01:34:32,350 --> 01:34:37,850
Undoubtedly, unequivocally,
unabashedly, yes.

1251
01:34:37,950 --> 01:34:40,850
And for one week,

1252
01:34:40,950 --> 01:34:45,700
one week in my sad little
blip of an existence...

1253
01:34:48,000 --> 01:34:50,500
it made me happy.

1254
01:34:52,200 --> 01:34:53,600
That's a good answer.

1255
01:34:53,700 --> 01:34:56,200
Rubbish, we don't want to be happy.
We want to be famous.

1256
01:34:56,300 --> 01:34:58,800
Yeah! What's all this "Is she the one" tripe?

1256
01:34:58,900 --> 01:35:00,000
Take his brain!

1257
01:35:00,100 --> 01:35:03,950
No, don't take the brain!
Don't take the brain, mice!

1258
01:35:13,100 --> 01:35:14,700
It wasn't me!

1259
01:35:14,800 --> 01:35:16,650
I'm famous.

1260
01:35:16,750 --> 01:35:19,100
Shoot him, quickly, shoot him!

1261
01:35:19,200 --> 01:35:20,700
Oh, bollocks!

1263
01:35:29,750 --> 01:35:31,200
I'm gonna be sick.

1264
01:35:34,500 --> 01:35:35,700
Belgium.

1265
01:35:44,650 --> 01:35:46,100
Follow me.

1266
01:35:46,750 --> 01:35:49,250
Left, right, left, right.

1267
01:35:49,400 --> 01:35:51,850
Attention!

1268
01:35:55,350 --> 01:35:58,300
Thanks a lot for leaving me behind.

1269
01:35:58,400 --> 01:36:00,650
Though I can't say I blame you.

1270
01:36:00,750 --> 01:36:04,450
Mr. President, we're here for your protection.

1271
01:36:04,550 --> 01:36:06,850
Oh, hey, thanks, man. I appreciate it.

1272
01:36:06,950 --> 01:36:08,300
Fire!

1273
01:36:10,100 --> 01:36:11,750
No! No!

1274
01:36:14,750 --> 01:36:16,850
I don't see what all the fuss is about.

1275
01:36:16,950 --> 01:36:19,800
Vogons are the worst marksmen
in the galaxy.

1276
01:36:19,900 --> 01:36:25,000
- For God's sake, stop!
- Cease fire.

1277
01:36:31,650 --> 01:36:36,150
Now I've got a headache...

1278
01:36:44,350 --> 01:36:46,350
Marvin!

1279
01:36:46,450 --> 01:36:47,650
Oh, no!

1280
01:36:50,000 --> 01:36:53,200
He's got a towel. Run away!

1281
01:36:55,450 --> 01:36:58,400
I'm gonna get us outta here.
How do you drive this thing?

1281
01:36:58,500 --> 01:37:00,500
Hey, what's going on?

1282
01:37:02,250 --> 01:37:04,500
We need that gun.

1283
01:37:05,400 --> 01:37:08,300
Come on, let's get this ship started.
Come on, start!

1284
01:37:09,400 --> 01:37:11,450
Come on. Oh, fire, fire!

1285
01:37:11,600 --> 01:37:12,900
Fire, fire!

1287
01:37:17,500 --> 01:37:19,750
Oh, he's locked the gate
from the other side.

1288
01:37:19,850 --> 01:37:21,950
We'll have to go the other way.

1289
01:37:22,050 --> 01:37:24,000
Come on, let's go!

1290
01:37:29,300 --> 01:37:31,800
Stop!

1291
01:37:34,050 --> 01:37:36,050
Oh, no!

1292
01:37:37,850 --> 01:37:42,000
Stop it! Stop it!
Stop shooting at us! Stop it!

1293
01:38:01,100 --> 01:38:04,750
Oh, I feel so depressed.

1294
01:38:06,150 --> 01:38:11,100
- I can't face another day.
- I feel so depressed.

1295
01:38:12,950 --> 01:38:14,750
What's the point?

1296
01:38:22,800 --> 01:38:25,050
- You all right?
- Yeah.

1297
01:38:30,750 --> 01:38:33,650
Sorry about your spaceship, Arthur.

1298
01:38:39,200 --> 01:38:41,400
Marvin, you saved our lives.

1299
01:38:41,500 --> 01:38:44,750
I know. Wretched, isn't it?

1300
01:38:50,250 --> 01:38:53,250
You got to ask yourself, what's the point?

1301
01:38:53,400 --> 01:38:56,000
Take it away.

1302
01:39:03,700 --> 01:39:08,950
You could do all of that, but it's not gonna...
Well, I'll ask... I'll just ask.

1303
01:39:09,100 --> 01:39:12,900
I've just been informed by some of the lads...

1304
01:39:13,000 --> 01:39:15,400
- ...that since we're so near completion...
- Yeah?

1305
01:39:15,500 --> 01:39:17,850
...we're gonna go ahead and finish Earth.

1306
01:39:17,950 --> 01:39:19,500
- Oh!
- So...

1307
01:39:19,600 --> 01:39:23,600
We, well, we can put it back exactly
as it was when you left, you know.

1308
01:39:23,700 --> 01:39:27,050
Unless there's...

1309
01:39:27,150 --> 01:39:30,650
there's, you know, anything
you want to change.

1310
01:39:32,800 --> 01:39:38,100
Something you think
your planet could do without.

1311
01:39:39,550 --> 01:39:42,850
Yeah. Me.

1312
01:39:43,300 --> 01:39:45,550
Oh! Hello?

1313
01:39:45,650 --> 01:39:49,350
No, as is. Yep, leave it. Yep.

1314
01:39:51,300 --> 01:39:52,900
Let's go somewhere.

1315
01:39:53,000 --> 01:39:55,600
Definitely. Where did you have in mind?

1316
01:39:55,700 --> 01:39:58,900
I know this great restaurant
at the end of the universe.

1317
01:39:59,050 --> 01:40:02,050
I am a little peckish.

1318
01:40:04,050 --> 01:40:06,800
I need to go to Humma's.
He's got something of mine.

1319
01:40:06,900 --> 01:40:08,100
I think.

1319
01:40:09,000 --> 01:40:12,550
- I'm so confused.
- Don't worry, baby. We'll sort it out.

1320
01:40:12,650 --> 01:40:16,300
All right, let's trip the light fantastic, baby.
Just you and me.

1321
01:40:16,400 --> 01:40:18,250
Come on.

1322
01:40:18,350 --> 01:40:22,400
- You got your towel?
- Yeah. Why? Am I gonna need it?

1323
01:40:22,500 --> 01:40:25,950
- Only always.
- Right. Yeah.

1324
01:40:26,050 --> 01:40:29,500
'Cause I wouldn't wanna go anywhere
without my wonderful towel.

1325
01:40:35,050 --> 01:40:37,950
Okay. Hold tight.

1326
01:40:41,450 --> 01:40:46,650
<i>Stand by for commencement
of life cycle. In three, two, one...</i>

1327
01:40:46,750 --> 01:40:49,000
<i>All right!</i>

1328
01:41:32,850 --> 01:41:35,100
Not that anyone cares what I say,

1329
01:41:35,200 --> 01:41:38,450
but the restaurant is
at the other end of the universe.

1332
01:44:53,800 --> 01:44:58,050
<i>It is, of course, well known
that careless talk costs lives.</i>

1333
01:44:58,150 --> 01:45:01,250
<i>But the full scale of the problem
is not always appreciated.</i>

1334
01:45:01,350 --> 01:45:05,000
<i>For instance, at the very moment
that Arthur Dent said...</i>

1335
01:45:05,100 --> 01:45:08,650
<i>"I wouldn't want to go anywhere
without my wonderful towel",</i>

1336
01:45:08,750 --> 01:45:13,300
<i>a freak wormhole opened up in the
fabric of the space-time continuum</i>

1337
01:45:13,400 --> 01:45:16,900
<i>and carried his words far, far back in time,</i>

1338
01:45:17,000 --> 01:45:21,000
<i>across almost infinite reaches
of space, to a distant galaxy,</i>

1339
01:45:21,100 --> 01:45:24,800
<i>where strange and warlike beings
were poised on the brink</i>

1340
01:45:24,900 --> 01:45:27,350
<i>of frightful interstellar battle.</i>

1341
01:45:27,450 --> 01:45:32,000
<i>The two opposing leaders, resplendent
in their black-jeweled battle shorts</i>

1342
01:45:32,100 --> 01:45:34,100
<i>were meeting for the last time,</i>

1343
01:45:34,250 --> 01:45:37,000
<i>when a dreadful silence fell.</i>

1344
01:45:37,100 --> 01:45:39,050
<i>And at that very moment,</i>

1345
01:45:39,150 --> 01:45:43,150
<i>the words "I wouldn't want to go
anywhere without my wonderful towel"</i>

1346
01:45:43,300 --> 01:45:46,250
<i>drifted across the conference table.</i>

1347
01:45:46,350 --> 01:45:49,000
<i>Unfortunately, in their native tongue,</i>

1348
01:45:49,100 --> 01:45:52,100
<i>this was the most appalling
insult imaginable.</i>

1349
01:45:52,200 --> 01:45:53,800
<i>So, the two opposing battle fleets</i>

1350
01:45:53,900 --> 01:45:56,500
<i>decided to settle their few
remaining differences,</i>

